<html>
<title><b><c>Jean-Baptiste de La Salle<c><b></title>

<body>
1. He was canonized by Pope Leo XIII on May 24, 1900.

2. He was proclaimed as the Patron Saint of Teachers on May 15, 1950, by Pope Pius XII. 

3. He is considered the founder of the first Catholic schools.

4. He died because of hard work and service.

5. He didn't expect to live with the teachers.

6. De La Salle was a pioneer in programs for training lay teachers.

7. He founded what is generally considered the first normal school.

8. He died at Saint Yon near Rouen early in 1719 on Good Friday.

9. John Baptist was the eldest child of Louis de la Salle and Nicolle de Moet de Brouillet.

10. He took the degree of Master of Arts.
</body>
